<FIRST>r i AM-Soviet-SubwayBombs     04-22 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Soviet-Subway Bombs,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Homemade Bombs Discovered In Subway Stations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities defused two homemade bombs, one with a
timing device, found in Moscow subway stations, a Foreign Ministry
spokesman said Friday.
   Gennady I. Gerasimov said the first device was spotted by
passengers in a subway car at the Paveletskaya station. ``The bag
seemed to belong to no one and contained a plastic bag wrapped in a
newspaper,'' he said.
   KGB officers and subway security personnel found a pipe bomb
inside the bag, Gerasimov said. The device was attached to an
electric alarm clock and wired with batteries, he said.
   A similar device, without a clock, was discovered about an hour
later at the Vdnkh metro station, the spokesman said.
   ``Both episodes appear to be linked,'' Gerasimov said. ``The KGB
has begun an investigation.''
</TEXT>
