<HEAD>Senate Panel to Hold Hearings on Ship Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Senate Armed Services Committee will hold
hearings on the explosion aboard the USS Iowa that killed 47 seamen.
   Sens. Sam Nunn, D-Ga., the chairman, and the ranking Republican,
John Warner of Virginia, said on Friday the hearings will begin
after the Navy's board of inquiry completes its probe into the
accident.
   The hearings will focus on safety procedures used in the past,
whether changes in the procedures are necessary and possible
