<NOTE>___</NOTE>
<NOTE>Active-Duty Strength Drops in March</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The active-duty strength of the nation's armed
forces dropped slightly last month.
   In all, the Army, Navy, Marine Corps and Air Force reported
2,116,889 men and women on active duty as of March 31, down from
the 2,122,636 on Feb. 28, according to Pentagon figures released on
Friday.
   A year ago, on March 31, 1988, the Pentagon reported 2,141,757
men and women in uniform.
   A reduction was ordered in early 1988 by the Reagan
administration. Most of the reductions were made through changes in
recruiting goals, tighter re-enlistment standards and ``early out''
incentives.
</TEXT>
