   From ``Star Wars'' to ad wars: George Lucas'
special effects company has begun making commercials for the small
screen.
   Lucasfilm Ltd. announced Friday it had formed an advertising
division that will tap the expertise that went into such movies as
the ``Star Wars'' series and the fantasy ``Willow.''
   The first project currently under way in England is a series of
four spots touting Bell Atlantic, the regional telephone company,
said Peter Friedman, who is heading Lucasfilm Commercial
Productions. The advertisements will combine computer graphics,
animation and live action _ ``a technique that's never been used
before,'' Friedman said.
   The operation will use the resources of Industrial Light &amp;
Magic, the computer graphics division of Lucasfilm.
