<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Baseball slugger Jose Canseco, who in
February was ticketed for driving his car 120 mph in Florida, has
been charged with felony possession of a loaded semiautomatic
handgun.
   Canseco was ``totally cooperative'' when arrested Friday at the
University of California's Laurel Heights campus while returning to
his car after a medical exam, said campus police Lt. Mark Kurtz. A
passerby had noticed the weapon on the floor of Canseco's parked
Jaguar, he said.
   Canseco was released after several hours when his wife, Esther,
posted $5,000 bail. He will be arraigned in three weeks.
   Kurtz said police could find no permit on file allowing Canseco
to carry a weapon but they are continuing to investigate.
   The 24-year-old right fielder went to the Oakland Coliseum later
Friday and suited up for a game against the California Angels. He
has been sidelined with an injured left wrist.
