<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     04-22 0440</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0452</SECOND>
<HEAD>Snow Over Northern New England; Scattered Showers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell over northern New England and rain showers were
scattered over parts of the Northwest and West early today, but
most areas of the nation were dry.
   Rain dampened the eastern coast of Florida, northeastern South
Dakota to west-central Minnesota, western Montana to the Idaho
panhandle, southwest Oregon and northeast California. A strong
thunderstorm developed over southwest Minnesota during the morning.
   An inch of snow fell at Mount Washington in New Hampshire in the
six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT, but no significant rainfall was
recorded around the nation during the same period.
   Warnings have been posted for fire danger over the lower
elevations of Colorado, which has had high temperatures, a dry
spell and gusty winds.
   The high temperature for the nation on Friday was 105 degrees at
Buckeye, Ariz.
   Today's forecast: rainshowers reaching from the northern Pacific
Coast across Montana; snow extending over the Green and White
Mountains of northern New England and over northeast New York; and
dry weather for much of the nation.
   High temperatures were expected in the 30s and 40s over New
England, inland New York, and much of Michigan; in the 50s and 60s
from southeast New York across the Virginias, the remainder of the
Great Lakes, the Ohio Valley, Wisconsin, northeast Minnesota, the
northern half of the Rockies, the northern half of the Plateau and
the northern half of the Pacific Coast; and in the 90s from
southwest Nebraska across much of Kansas, western Oklahoma, the
western third of Texas, southern New Mexico, southern Arizona and
southeast California. High temperatures for much of the rest of the
country were to reach the 70s and 80s.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 26
degrees at Marquette, Mich., to 87 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 62 fair; Boston 49 fair; Buffalo 35 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 57 fair; Cincinnati 58 partly cloudy; Cleveland
40 fair; Detroit 41 fair; Miami 70 fair; New York 55 fair;
Philadelphia 51 fair; Pittsburgh 45 fair; Portland, Maine, 41
showery; Washington 57 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 60 partly cloudy; Chicago 49 cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 73 fair; Denver 67 partly cloudy; Des Moines 66
fair; Indianapolis 59 fair; Kansas City 70 fair; Minneapolis-St.
Paul 57 partly cloudy; Nashville 57 fair; New Orleans 65 foggy; St.
Louis 67 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 66 partly cloudy; Anchorage 42 partly cloudy;
Las Vegas 79 windy; Los Angeles 60 fair; Salt Lake City 69 partly
cloudy; San Diego 63 fair; San Francisco 51 fair; Seattle 50 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 32 fair; Toronto 30 fair.
</TEXT>
