<TEXT>
   Former Secretary of State George P. Shultz
was among six people honored Saturday by a veterans group for
services to veterans and the country.
   The American Veterans of World War II, Korea and Vietnam gave
their Silver Helmet Peace Award to Shultz, who headed the State
Department for 6{ years in the Reagan administration.
   Shultz was cited for ``contributions to improved international
relations.''
