the Silver Helmet Humanitarianism Award for raising money for the
hungry and to send cancer-striken children to summer camp ``in the
highest traditions of the American way of life.''
   Raymond L. Hess of Youngstown, Ohio, was honored s ``AMVET of
the year'' for exceptional leadership. A life member of the group,
he has held every office in his hometown post and has served as
state commander.
