<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--OzoneProtest     04-22 0143</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Ozone Protest,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>Demonstrators Punch Holes In Symbolic Ozone</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Demonstrators dressed as aerosal cans and
refrigerators raced up a church stairway Saturday and burst through
a paper-covered hoop, symbolically depicting the depletion of the
Earth's ozone layer.
   A crowd of about 1,000 people watched as about 20 costumed
activists staged the protest to mark ``Earth Day,'' a day of
environmental awareness called by ecological groups worldwide.
   The demonstration was held at the Spanish Steps, a 137-step
staircase to the Trinita Dei Monti church.
   Organizers said the demonstration re-enacted the effects on the
ozone layer of chlorofluorocarbons, compounds used in aerosol spray
cans and refrigerators.
   The ozone layer protects Earth from cancer-causing untraviolet
light.
   Beniamino Bonardi, national director of the Environmental League
of Italy, said the demonstration sought to publicize efforts to
make the government ban the use of chlorofluorocarbons.
