   Officials said two of the suspects were charged with attempted
murder and the third with driving in a dangerous manner. The three,
who were not identified, were jailed pending a court hearing.
   Police gave this account:
   Three men attempted to carry out a credit-card fraud at the
Advance Bank in downtown Sydney shortly after 3 p.m.
   When police responded to an alarm from the bank one man sprayed
officers with mace but he was overpowered.
   His two accomplices, wearing women's clothes, fled in a
limousine and led police cruisers on a chase through central
Sydney, colliding with seven other cars and allegedly hitting a
detective before they were stopped in nearby Darlinghurst.
   The detective was reported in satisfactory condition at Sydney
Hospital.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
